<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/21001AHGQKHHCBJDNTTTMDTTPLSBDJSQB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Anything Goes";
  schema:description """
	<h2><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Anything Goes</span></span></h2>Music & Lyrics by Cole Porter <span><br/></span>Original Book by P.G. Wodehouse & Guy Bolton and Howard Lindsay & Russel Crouse. <span><br/></span>New Book by Timothy Crouse & John Weidman<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All aboard! Reno Sweeney, a nightclub singer, and second-rate conman Moonface Martin (aka “Public Enemy #13”), have boarded the SS American sailing to London—but this voyage will be like no other. They must help lovestruck pal Billy Crocker win the heart of heiress Hope Harcourt, all while evading police, gangsters and feisty stowaways.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Join Reno and the rest of the crew for song, dance and the madcap antics of this musical theatre classic!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Director–Cathy Wilmot<span><br/></span>Choreography–Keri Minty<span><br/></span>Musical Direction– Caitlin Hayes<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.caputheatre.com/\">CapU Theatre Website</a></h2><span><br/></span>Relaxed Performance: Saturday April 03<span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.capilanou.ca/media/capilanouca/student-life/capu-community/blueshore-financial-centre-for-performing-arts/documents/Visual-Story.pdf\">Visual Story for the Theatre</a>
""";
