<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/20001ASSPTTDVHQJLHCGJGTSBBKPHTPJB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Julius Caesar";
  schema:description """
	<h2><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Julius Caesar</span></span></h2>by William Shakespeare<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A modern-day capital city of the most powerful country in the world. A general returns home who commands not only armies but a near-fanatical popularity with the people. This adulation Caesar enjoys disturbs others, however—politicians, other generals, and even his friends worry he may become a tyrant. They hatch a plot to assassinate him. It’s for the greater good, after all.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A relentless political thriller, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Julius Caesar</span> explores the question of how far is too far to defeat a political rival, while taking the audience on a wild ride through the halls of power, prophecy, and the devastation of war.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Directed by Bob Frazer<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.caputheatre.com/\">CapU Theatre Website</a></h2><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Relaxed Performance: Saturday February 13<span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.capilanou.ca/media/capilanouca/student-life/capu-community/blueshore-financial-centre-for-performing-arts/documents/Visual-Story.pdf\">Visual Story for the Theatre</a><span><br/></span>
""";
