<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/19401AJHGNGSSNHVHGVRMMRHQDRBGPQPM>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Louisa May Alcott's Little Women";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">THE COMING-OF-AGE FAVOURITE</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Independent Jo, traditional Meg, shy Beth, and vivacious Amy are navigating the difficulties of young adulthood during the Civil War. Despite having varying ideas of what it means to be a woman; the March sisters together find strength to forge their own paths. This enduring story of friendship, romance, loss, and personal discovery has charmed generations. Fall in love with Louisa May Alcott’s relatable and radiant characters as they come to life in this shining adaptation.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">CONTENT ADVISORY</span>⚠️<span><br/></span>This production may contain flashing lights and water-based haze and fog. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">RUN TIME</span><span><br/></span>Approx. 2h 35m (including one intermission)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
